From NWS Survey...This weak EF0 tornado touched down near Highway 43 and Matlock Road in eastern Madison county and tracked 4.6 miles and dissipated at Red Dog Road in western Leake county. Tree damage, from a handful of uprooted trees, were the main damage at the very beginning of the path. The remaining damage was mostly small/large limbs down along Red Dog Road and the Natchez Trace. One large limb downed a power line. Max winds were 85 mph (EF0) and total path length was 4.6 miles.
